## A.6 Three decisions needed before Phase B teardown

| # | Decision | Options |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | **p0 routed-interface fabric ask** | (a) Ask network team for a third change — convert Eth1/23 and Eth1/25 to routed /31s with BGP. Adds ~1 week if their queue is slow. <br>(b) Deploy HBN with single-path BGP only (p1 only). TC4 ECMP scaling will be flat — report it as "HBN deployed and BGP works on one uplink; cannot demonstrate multi-uplink ECMP without further fabric reconfig." Honest but unimpressive. |
| 2 | **EVPN approach** | (a) Keep enabled locally; leaf won't advertise EVPN. Probably fine, may or may not work. <br>(b) Strip EVPN from startupYAMLJ2 entirely. Cleaner; HBN container has no EVPN code path. |
| 3 | **IPAM conflict resolution** | (a) Drop `12-fabric-host-config.yaml` from the HBN cluster profile addon list so host PFs don't get static 172.16.97.10/.11 IPs. **Recommended.** <br>(b) Override pool1 to a non-conflicting subnet. Works but loses the "everything in 172.16.97/24" tidy underlay. |

My recommendations:
- 1: **(a) request the third fabric change** — without it, HBN's ECMP value-prop can't be demonstrated. Worth the wait. Meanwhile, leave VPC-OVN running (data already collected).
- 2: **(a) keep EVPN on** — try first; if HBN container fails to start with no EVPN peer, fall back to stripping it.
- 3: **(a) drop the host-IP manifest** from the HBN profile — cleanest fix, matches HBN's expected topology (host traffic flows via HBN, not directly via host PF).

